<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key C, 4/4. Opens on Am pickup. Descending melody of Psalm 67 character.
- E major (secondary dominant to Am) kept as ③ label.
- LH "33" triads, half-note rhythm throughout. RH light thirds.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- LH bass descends Am→G→F→G in bars 1-5; contrasts ascending melody.
- Bridge bars 7-10 oscillates G-F-G-Am for stability.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Quiet Am opening; builds bars 1-6; broad G bridge 7-11; converges to C cadence 13-15.
-->
